ror Diocletian  at the beginning of the 4th century. The popular legend in which the hero slays a dragon is a medieval Italian invention. He was for a long time a more important saint in the Orthodox Church than in the West, and the name was not much used in England during the Middle Ages, even after  St George  came to be regarded as the patron of England in the 14th century. Its use increased from the 1400s, and by  1500  it was regularly among the most popular male names. This popularity was reinforced when  George I  came to the throne in  1714 , bringing this name with him from Germany. It has been one of the most popular English boys' names ever since."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs George Eaton was born about 1397, in Ickworth, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. She married George Eyton about 1417, in Ickworth, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"Abt 1397–":"umbes 1397–Surnud","1393–Male":"1393–Surnud","1419–1476":"1419–1476","1397–Female":"1397–Surnud","1476":"1476","Abt 1397":"umbes 1397","1397":"1397","1393":"1393","1419":"1419","Abt 1417":"umbes 1417","Ickworth, Suffolk, England":"Ickworth, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Thorndon, Mid Suffolk District, Suffolk, England":"Thorndon, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1397–":"noin 1397–Kuollut","1393–Male":"1393–Kuollut","1419–1476":"1419–1476","1397–Female":"1397–Kuollut","1476":"1476","Abt 1397":"noin 1397","1397":"1397","1393":"1393","1419":"1419","Abt 1417":"noin 1417","Ickworth, Suffolk, England":"Ickworth, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Thorndon, Mid Suffolk District, Suffolk, England":"Thorndon, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1397–":"environ 1397–Décédée","1393–Male":"1393–Décédé","1419–1476":"1419–1476","1397–Female":"1397–Décédée","1476":"1476","Abt 1397":"environ 1397","1397":"1397","1393":"1393","1419":"1419","Abt 1417":"environ 1417","Ickworth, Suffolk, England":"Ickworth, Suffolk